cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques to identify contradictions and disagreements in medical guidelines. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with NLP and its applications, which is the main focus of this paper. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems, which is relevant to the NLP system described in this paper. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data, which is relevant to the information retrieval modules used in the system. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category deals with the retrieval of relevant information from large collections of data, which is a key component of the system described in this paper. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): This sub-category deals with the social and ethical implications of computing technologies, which may be relevant to the use of automated systems in medical decision-making.
